cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR. 

The paper deals with automatic data collection of structured visual facts from images with captions, which involves computer vision (CV) and natural language processing (NLP) techniques. Therefore, cs.CV and cs.CL are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also uses machine learning (ML) algorithms to achieve high accuracy in fact annotation, which makes cs.AI and cs.LG likely sub-categories as well. Finally, the paper involves information retrieval (IR) techniques to localize visual facts in images, which makes cs.IR a possible sub-category.
